<main class="connect-shell"><section class="connect-card"><div class="connect-copy"><p class="eyebrow">One-time secure connection</p><h1>Sign in inside the isolated YouTube Studio browser.</h1><p>The remote browser runs on the backend server. Enter Google credentials only inside YouTube/Google pages. YouTubePilot saves encrypted browser session state—not your password.</p><ol><li>Open the remote studio.</li><li>Complete Google login, OTP, CAPTCHA or channel selection.</li><li>Wait until the YouTube Studio dashboard appears.</li><li>Return here and save the encrypted connection.</li></ol><div class="warning-box">The connection window expires at <strong><%= new Date(session.expiresAt).toLocaleTimeString() %></strong>. Only one connection window can run on this server at a time.</div></div><div class="connect-actions"><a class="btn btn-primary btn-xl" href="<%= session.remoteUrl %>" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Open remote YouTube Studio ↗</a><form method="post" action="/app/youtube/complete"><input type="hidden" name="_csrf" value="<%= csrfToken %>"><button class="btn btn-success btn-xl" type="submit">Save encrypted connection</button></form><form method="post" action="/app/youtube/cancel"><input type="hidden" name="_csrf" value="<%= csrfToken %>"><button class="btn btn-ghost" type="submit">Cancel connection</button></form></div></section></main><%- include('partials/footer') %>
